This paper is about developing semantic parsers, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves training neural networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multiple knowledge-bases (KBs) also suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
